examples.en: The danger of war has eased off.
He eased himself into a chair.
A priest has eased me of my sins.
The rain had eased off a bit.
He eased his foot off the accelerator.
As the day drew on, the shelling eased off a bit.
Modern machinery has significantly eased the backbreaking work of farming.
He eased himself into the chair.
Jean eased back on the pillows and relaxed.
He undid the padlock and eased back the lid.
She eased the ball-shaped doodad back into its socket.
Her sympathy eased the hurt he felt after his dog's death.
The morphine was starting to take effect and the pain eased.
I waited until my initial wrath had eased before voicing my complaint.
